In a study examining the tuberculin conversion rate in a group of long-term aid workers from New Zealand, the TB conversion rate was 1.4 per 1000 person-months.20 Despite this rate of newly infected persons, active TB cases are very rare.4 The average conversion rate varies among different regions and countries (Tables 35.2
and 35.3
).

Posttravel follow-up is unfortunately a neglected topic. Emotional and physical aspects of the volunteer should be addressed to ensure proper resettlement into his or her culture and community (Tables 35.9
and 35.10
).
